    "severity": "Sev-2 (High)",
    "description": "Unexpected Long Running Job incident on the Store Sales pipeline (RTL_STS_ULRJ): store Sales POS Kafka daily rollup unexpectedly long.",
    "symptoms": "Daily POS sales rollup from Kafka went from 20min to 1h45m across 450 stores.",
    "root_cause": "A firmware update pushed to 90 POS terminals began emitting duplicate heartbeat events, inflating the topic partition size the consumer must scan by ~6x.",
    "business_impact": "Delayed store performance dashboards for regional managers' morning huddles.",
    "resolution": "Add dedup filter keyed on transaction_id + terminal_id + timestamp at the Kafka consumer level; roll back or patch firmware."
  },
